Recently I was working on raising my pottery, and noticed something&#xD;
somewhat annoying.&amp;nbsp; Some recipies in the database return things&#xD;
like "Sculpting Tools", etc, after the combined item.&amp;nbsp; I don't&#xD;
recall seeing this on other recipies (but I may be mistaken).&amp;nbsp; &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
My request is - can you set it up such that the *always* returned item&#xD;
(Smithing Hammer, Corking Device, Sculpting Tools, Planing Device, etc)&#xD;
are always returned 1st?&amp;nbsp; It's a minor thing, but it caused me&#xD;
untold grief when I had to delete (or drop) every worthless unfired&#xD;
item I made before I could auto-inventory my Sculpting Tools.&amp;nbsp; I&#xD;
must've destroyed 40 (Scuplting Tools) last night.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
I'd love to be able to auto inventory the Sculpting Tools 1st, and then&#xD;
destroy the item, or simply let it fall to the ground.&amp;nbsp; Etc for&#xD;
similar skills.&amp;nbsp; Yes I'm lazy, but its little things like this&#xD;
being changed since your tenure that have made me actually pick up&#xD;
Tradeskills after 7years of avoiding them.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Minor thoughts as I work on Brewing and Pottery-&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
- Celestial Essence stacking to 100 &lt;br&gt;&#xD;
- NPC who will enchant/imbue (clay, metals, vials, gems, etc) - I felt&#xD;
