    <item>
      <title>Re: Items Returned on Combines - A Request!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=17460#M17460</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;My brother taught me a system for dealing with sculpting tools.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Leave the bag that has the sculpting tools in it open next to (or overlapping) the tradeskill interface.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Click combine, then move the cursor to click on the (now empty) bag slot &lt;STRONG&gt;twice&lt;/STRONG&gt;. Then move the cursor again to click the auto inventory button.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The first click drops your newly created item in the bag, the second click drops the sculpting tools in the bag, and picks up the new item.&amp;nbsp; Then clicking auto inventory drops the new item on the ground.&amp;nbsp; If you fail the combine, the first click drops the sculpting tools, the second click picks it up, and clicking auto inventory puts it back again.&amp;nbsp; Of course, even doing this, sooner or later you will miss click and drop your tools.&amp;nbsp; But that's why I buy 2-3 sculpting tools when I do a set of combines.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Nov 2006 21:42:03 GMT</pubDate>
